<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1605,1892]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,1679,1705]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
. The specimens from the Selwyn River agree well with 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1983" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1983" box="[967,1295,1680,1706]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Abelaturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornophorus">
<emphasis box="[967,1150,1680,1705]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">A. cornophorus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[1156,1295,1680,1706]" pageId="17" pageNumber="33" refString="Cook, R. D. (1983) Rheophilic and hyporheic water mites of New Zealand. Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, 21 (2), 1 - 224." type="journal article" year="1983">
Cook, 
<number box="[1234,1295,1680,1706]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in having a relatively deeper capitular bay and pointed projections on the margin of the ventral shield (except for one female which bears a well developed projection on one side of the body, see 
<figureCitation box="[1053,1159,1754,1780]" captionStart="FIGURE 13 A – C" captionStartId="18.[151,261,1368,1392]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,205,1332]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,194,1347]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 13 A – C. Abelaturus c ornophorus Cook, 1983 (A = male, B – C = female): A, C = ventral shield; B = anterodorsal portion of ventral shield. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/193575/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Fig. 
<number box="[1107,1137,1754,1780]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="13.0">13</number>
C
</figureCitation>
). Differences are found in the rectangular hood at the anterior end of the ventral shield (
<figureCitation box="[937,1046,1792,1818]" captionStart="FIGURE 13 A – C" captionStartId="18.[151,261,1368,1392]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,205,1332]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,194,1347]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 13 A – C. Abelaturus c ornophorus Cook, 1983 (A = male, B – C = female): A, C = ventral shield; B = anterodorsal portion of ventral shield. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/193575/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Fig. 
<number box="[995,1025,1792,1818]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="13.0">13</number>
B
</figureCitation>
) and the first coxae being more truncate at the tips. The variability of further populations needs to be examined to clarify the taxonomy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
